Canada plans a three part, one billiondlr issue Tuesday, which will be dated and delivered May 1, thefinance department said. The bonds will be issued as follows.    - 8-1/2 pct bonds due March 1, 1992,    - 8-3/4 pct bonds due June 1, 1996,    - 9 pct bonds due March 1, 2011.    The nine pct bonds will be issued to a maximum of 325 mlndlrs. The Bank of Canada will buy a minimum of 100 mln dlrs ofthe new issue, including five mln dlrs of the 2011 maturity. Reuter&#3;